m_previousSegment

The SegmentLayout previous to this along the x-axis; null if this is the leftmost segment in the row specified by #m_segmentIndex.

m_isGhost

boolean m_isGhost
true if this SegmentLayout serves as a placeholder for a column structure that spans multiple rows; see FormLayout.addMultiRow(...).

m_lastGhost

If this is a ghost, m_lastGhost identifies the index of the RowLayout in which the last ghost of the multi-row structure is contained.

Class org.hs.jfc.FormLayout implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

m_hgap

int m_hgap
The gaps along the x-axis between the components.

m_vgap

int m_vgap
The gaps along the y-axis between the components.

m_pct

double m_pct
Justification percentage: consider a value that is m_pct of the difference between the actual width of a component and the width it would have to be to right-justify with the rest of the column. If this value is large enough to extend the component such that it right-justifies, then do so; otherwise leave it as is. Default is 0.

m_refreshMinimum

boolean m_refreshMinimum
This flag indicates that the locations and sizes for all the components in the minimum layout scenario must be recalculated.

m_refreshPreferred

boolean m_refreshPreferred
This flag indicates that the locations and sizes for all the components in the preferred layout scenario must be recalculated.

m_Columns

hVector m_Columns
The ColumnLayouts that govern the x-coordinates of all components governed by this FormLayout.

m_ColumnLeader

FormLayout.ColumnLeader m_ColumnLeader
A invisible entity that sits at the right end of the ColumnLayouts.

m_RowLeader

FormLayout.RowLeader m_RowLeader
An invisible entity that sits at the bottom of the linked list of RowLayouts; all recursive row operations start here.

m_container

Container m_container
The object that has employed this FormLayout to lay out its components.

m_ListOfAddedComponents

Vector m_ListOfAddedComponents
A collection of the components contained in this FormPanel, in the chronological order in which the components were added to the layout.

Class org.hs.generator.GArrayAccess implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

array

GExpression array
The array field represents the base of the array access expression, and hence must evaluate to an array type. Considering the example above, the local variable numbers would be an appropriate value for this field.

index

GExpression index
The index field represents the index within square brackets, and hence must evaluate to a primitive of type int. Considering again the example above, the constant value 3 represents the index in that GArrayAccess expression.

Class org.hs.generator.GCatch implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

catchWhat

GVariable catchWhat
The variable to catch, which, like a parameter, is expected to have prefix and initializer set to null, isLocal set to true, and type set to some subclass of java.lang.Throwable. The variable's modifiers will be ignored.

body

GBlock body
The block to execute under the condition of the catch clause. The variable catchWhat will be available under the same terms as a parameter to a method.

Class org.hs.generator.GFor implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

init

GStatement init
The for loop initializer, such as 'int i = 0' in the example above. May be null. There must be some way to make this compound, but I'm not sure what that would be since I haven't tried it.

condition

GExpression condition
The for loop condition, such as 'i < something.size()' in the example above. May be null; if not, it must evaluate to a primitive boolean.

increment

Vector increment
A collection of GExpression, all appearing in the role of the line 'i++' in the example above. May be empty.

body

The body of the for loop.

Class org.hs.generator.GVariable implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

modifiers

int modifiers
The modifiers of the variable, as defined by java.lang.reflect.Modifier. Only used in the case that this GVariable represents a class field.

isLocal

boolean isLocal
Specify whether this GVariable is local to its context or not. Here are the rules:

Local:
- local variable - parameter

Not local:
- class field - this expression - super expression - class expression

Ignored for a length expression

type

GType type
The type of this GVariable. For special keywords, static types apply thus:

this: GType.THIS
super: GType.SUPER
class: GType.CLASS
length: GType.LENGTH

name

String name
The name of the variable; ignored for special keywords.

initializer

GExpression initializer
The initializer of the variable; ignored for parameters and special keywords.

prefix

GExpression prefix
The prefix of the variable; applies optionally to the keywords this and super, is required for the keywords class, length, and may not be applied to dynamic variables of any kind.

Vector variables
A collection of GVariable to declare in this single statement.
